  "area": "core",
  "body_sections": [
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Construct an array from an index array and a list of arrays to choose from."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "First of all, if confused or uncertain, definitely look at the Examples -\nin its full generality, this function is less simple than it might\nseem from the following code description:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "language": null,
          "text": "we.choose(a,c) == we.array([c[a[I]][I] for I in we.ndindex(a.shape)])",
          "type": "literal_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "But this omits some subtleties.  Here is a fully general summary:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Given an \"index\" array ("
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ") of integers and a sequence of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " arrays\n("
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "choices"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "), "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and each choice array are first broadcast, as necessary,\nto arrays of a common shape; calling these "
            },
            {
              "kind": "emphasis",
              "text": "Ba"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "kind": "emphasis",
              "text": "Bchoices[i], i =\n0,...,n-1"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " we have that, necessarily, "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Ba.shape == Bchoices[i].shape"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\nfor each "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "i"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ".  Then, a new array with shape "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "Ba.shape"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is created as\nfollows:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "if "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "mode='raise'"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " (the default), then, first of all, each element of\n"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " (and thus "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "Ba"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ") must be in the range "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "[0, n-1]"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "; now, suppose\nthat "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "i"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " (in that range) is the value at the "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "(j0, j1, ..., jm)"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "\nposition in "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "Ba"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " - then the value at the same position in the new array\nis the value in "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "Bchoices[i]"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " at that same position;"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "if "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "mode='wrap'"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ", values in "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " (and thus "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "Ba"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ") may be any (signed)\ninteger; modular arithmetic is used to map integers outside the range\n"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "[0, n-1]"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " back into that range; and then the new array is constructed\nas above;"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "if "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "mode='clip'"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ", values in "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " (and thus "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "Ba"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": ") may be any (signed)\ninteger; negative integers are mapped to 0; values greater than "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "n-1"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "\nare mapped to "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "n-1"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "; and then the new array is constructed as above."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ordered": false,
          "type": "list"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Extended Summary"
    },
